Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_interposer_route_block(25.10)            add_interposer_route_block(25.10)

Name
       add_interposer_route_block - Adds the clone blocks

Syntax
        add_interposer_route_block

       [-help]

       -cell <cell_name>

       -inst <clone_name>

       -location {<x y>}

       -orient {R0 R90 R180 R270 MX MY MX90 MY90}

       Adds  the  clone  blocks. It transforms the similar unrouted areas to a
       clone partition, which repeats the same routing pattern as  the  routed
       master  block.  This command enables you to replicate the routed master
       block multiple times with different orientations.

       Note: Before using the  add_interposer_route_block  command,  you  must
       launch  another  Innovus session for loading the initial DB followed by
       using create_interposer_route_block command to create the routed master
       block partition by specified box. This is used to generate master block
       partition and top DB.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the  master  cell  name  that  needs  to  be  repeated
              (string, required)

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each add_interposer_route_block parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:

              man add_interposer_route_block

       -inst <clone_name>
              Specifies the clone block name.

              Data_type: string, required

       -location {<x y>}
              Specifies the clone block's origin location.

              Note: The relative location between clone block's origin and the
              terms should exactly be the same with the master. Otherwise, the
              wire  of  clone  blocks will be shift accordingly after assemble
              design.

              Note: The snapping grid of the created block  honors  the  setF-
              PlanMode -snapBlockGrid command settings.

              Data_type: point, required

       -orient {R0 R90 R180 R270 MX MY MX90 MY90}
              Specifies  the  orientation of the clone block compared with the
              master.

              Data_type: enum, required

Examples
              * The following command replicates the routing  pattern  of  the
                master  cell (master_block) to the clone block (clone_block_1)
                at location x1 y1 at orientation R0.

                add_interposer_route_block    -cell     master_block     -inst
                clone_block_1 -location {x1 y1} -orient R0

              * The  following command repeats replicating the routing pattern
                of  the  master  cell  (master_block)  to  the   clone   block
                (clone_block_2) at location x2 y2 at orientation R180.

                add_interposer_route_block     -cell     master_block    -inst
                clone_block_2 -location {x2 y2} -orient R180

Related Information
